                            <comment id="12670093" author="fergus" created="Tue, 3 Feb 2009 20:14:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What is the difference between the HTMLStripTransformer and what is proposed here? Surely both would return:-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &quot;This text is bold and this text is underlined!&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12670099" author="shalinmangar" created="Tue, 3 Feb 2009 20:23:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No, not really. If HTML is embedded inside an XML document it needs to be encoded properly (replace &apos;&amp;lt;&apos; with &amp;lt; etc.). The example described here does not contain HTML, rather it contains XML nodes inside the &quot;xhtml : p&quot; node mixed with Text nodes. This is the same example which led to the discovery of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-999&quot; title=&quot;XPathRecordReader fails on XMLs with nodes mixed with CDATA content&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-999&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-999&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
